                     <origDate notBefore="1889" notAfter="1913">The late King <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/> (r. <date from="1872" to="1889">1872–89</date>) and the late <persName ref="PRS2012Arayas"/>, are mentioned the supplication formulas
                        throughout the manuscript. Also, King <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> (r. <date from="1889" to="1913">1889–1913</date>) is mentioned in the supplication formulas beginning from <locus target="#75rc"/> onwards. 
                        We may conjecture that at the time of preparing the manuscript <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/> and <persName ref="PRS2012Arayas"/> had been dead because the supplications call for prayer for the soul of both of them. 
                        This is not the case with the supplications dedicated to <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/>. 
                        <persName role="owner" ref="PRS14781GabraMikael"/> and <persName role="owner" ref="PRS14782TawaldaMadhen"/> are mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout the manuscript. 
                        In some supplication formulas, <foreign xml:lang="gez">daqiqa māḫbar</foreign> ‘children of the community’, that is, the Dabra Dāmmo monks together with the scribe <persName ref="PRS14757WaldaMikael"/> are mentioned. 
                        To consult <title ref="LIT2375Synaxa#FirstHalf"/> written by the same scribe, refer to <ref type="mss" corresp="ESdd013"/>.
                      </origDate>
